### Update an isolation segment

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/isolation_segments/[guid]" \
  -X PATCH \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -H "Content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{ "name": "my_isolation_segment" }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :isolation_segment_with_name, 'my_isolation_segment' %>
```

#### Definition
`PATCH /v3/isolation_segments/:guid`

#### Optional Parameters

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | -----------
**name** | _string_ | Name of the Isolation Segment.  Isolation Segment names must be unique across the entire system, and case is ignored when checking for uniqueness.

